{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"9f756ae8fe6b0254","type":"text","text":"Source Code","x":-1290,"y":5240,"width":150,"height":50},
		{"id":"bb63d8013f72e011","type":"text","text":"LLM","x":-930,"y":5213,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"a8803f0a9fd95e76","type":"text","text":"Database\n\nThe SQLLite object, Client, the Schema\n\nWhich has 2 tables mainly\n\nNodes and Edges\n","x":-2410,"y":4695,"width":402,"height":237},
		{"id":"66f9428c1da07235","type":"text","text":"LLM Client","x":-409,"y":4932,"width":250,"height":68},
		{"id":"30398bc26ea7a8dc","type":"text","text":"Agent","x":-364,"y":5586,"width":161,"height":51},
		{"id":"b0c0d8724f037949","type":"text","text":"invoke:\ninputs:\nuser prompt, optionally pydantic model\n\ndoes\ninvokes with a prompt and gets normal string response/pydantic model based on optional input, stores message in history, invoking this again continues the conversation\n\nreturns\nstring/pydantic model\n","x":10,"y":5060,"width":704,"height":292},
		{"id":"ed9805e5c35ddce4","type":"text","text":"invoke:\ninputs:\nuser prompt, optionally pydantic model\n\ndoes\nrun thes master agents which uses subagent to do research and output a final string/pydantic model to get make some kind of decision\n\nreturns\nstring/pydantic model\n","x":10,"y":5840,"width":704,"height":292},
		{"id":"c56e97d2b7b824a9","type":"text","text":"init: \ninputs:\nendpoint, model name, system prompt\n\ndoes\ninitiate langchain openai client\ninitiates an empty message history with system prompt\n\nreturns\nnull\n\n","x":50,"y":4640,"width":420,"height":292},
		{"id":"63a895509132e765","type":"text","text":"init: \ninputs:\nendpoint, model name, system prompt\ntools for quering\n\ndoes\ninitiate LLM Client\ninitiates an empty message history with system prompt\nMakes a subagent with tool access and it mangages those without making the history too long so it can make decisions\n\n\nreturns\nnull","x":50,"y":5414,"width":580,"height":343},
		{"id":"4d2cdd3c95483b91","type":"text","text":"Models\n\n---\n\nPydantic models shared by codebase for schema\n","x":-1359,"y":4894,"width":479,"height":166},
		{"id":"3b8d65f1828406eb","type":"text","text":"\n\nNode\n\nFields:\n- id: unique uuid\n- body: main markdown content\n- type: \n\t- endogenous: nodes made from source files, absolute, will need revision when new version are uploaded\n\t- exogenours: Nodes derived from above as agent cache, as the graph is queried with strong llms and user queries weak relationships will emerge, these will be made by this, at update time first all endogeneous nodes will be updated then the exogenous ones\n- original document name: {NOT SURE} the whole idea of a smart wiki is to no need to maintain a file system separately where we map nodes to it, so this is tentative, but i think we should keep this just in case for weak tether to where this node originally came from\n- keywords: keywords associated with this doc\n- Summary: A short summary of contents\n- Cluster: A dynamic group allocated to this node, where it bleongs (Manuals, company management docs etc) needs to be upated constantly this clustering is slightly wider scoped than original document name but narrower than type?\n- Embedding: embeddings for vector search of main body\n- summary_embeddings: embeddings for vector search of summary body\n\n\n---\n\n","x":-1880,"y":3840,"width":1180,"height":580},
		{"id":"2e57514a82b21b0e","type":"text","text":"Edge\n\nAn edge is a relationship between  two nodes\n\nFields:\n\nsource_node: uuid of original\ntarget_node: uuid or target\nlabel: how the target node is related to the original\n\n---\n\nstats\n\nAn object containing all statistical part of a graphs health\n\nTODO: Need to work on the most importatnt and easy to infer from, for a global graph and a node\n","x":-528,"y":3840,"width":998,"height":580},
		{"id":"85eecc40a54be070","type":"text","text":"Backend","x":-1880,"y":5292,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"96040228ef52bab0","type":"text","text":"Domain Engine","x":-2410,"y":5480,"width":180,"height":60},
		{"id":"42712b43d68def2b","type":"text","text":"\ninit:\ninput \npath to sqllite file\n\ndoes\ninitaites a global object, a runtime can only have one object which should be shared everwhere with contextvars and should be locked first before ops\nconnect to local file object of sqllite.\n\nreturn \nnull","x":-3409,"y":4754,"width":569,"height":366},
		{"id":"d49496a30d1c7ef1","type":"text","text":"\nquery:\ninputs\ntype: keyword/vector/id\nvalue: the actual query (always a string) (vectors will a string too, it will be converted to embedding this side only), or id of a node, it will be a string too, just uuid of that exact node.  So one string, can have three ways of lookups\n\ndoes\nif keywoard then does a keyword search: Nodes that contains that exact keyword (elastic serach or something?)\n\nvector search: Similarity search between all nodes/cluster roots? then give them a small summary of the highest matchers and their 1-2 hops?\n\nid: a node directly\n","x":-3409,"y":5225,"width":684,"height":458},
		{"id":"5fbd9277ba258153","type":"text","text":"recon\n\ninput:\na document md\n\ndoes\nGiven a doucment, search for whether it was ingested already, if yes then update all the nodes that were previously related to this, start with endogenous nodes, then go for exogeneous\n\nreturns\nscheduled jobs, either a document will go for sepration for ingest job, or it will go through a large cascading update, where existing nodes will be updated\n","x":-3405,"y":5810,"width":680,"height":375},
		{"id":"0dd2c3feb808f293","type":"text","text":"cascading_update\n\ninput\na large document, \n\ndoes\nwe will go through line ranges and fact check each node that share any similarity for any updates that needed to be done\n\nwe find any such node, we will start a cascading update which will update it then its neighbors, with newly updated information (for example if the node contains a company prop. library function signature) and a exogenous node exists which shows how to use it, both will be neededd to update it, or if another node refers to it, it will be needed to updated too\n\nouptut\nupdate jobs (see below)","x":-4540,"y":6100,"width":937,"height":400},
		{"id":"9ebdfcfe957015aa","type":"text","text":"\ningest\ninput\ngiven a node with only basics (body, type, summary, keywords, embeddings etc)\n\nDoes:\nLLM analyzes existing nodes and decides edges for both direction \n\noutputs\nEdge objects and which connect to existing nodes, bidirectional\n","x":-4540,"y":7320,"width":800,"height":280},
		{"id":"92f8a15c25973593","type":"text","text":"update: \ninput \nnode id\nbody\n\ndoes: \nupdates keywords/summaries, checkes edges etc if other needs updates too\n\noutput \nnull, just a confirmation and a scheduled job\n","x":-3976,"y":7840,"width":585,"height":300},
		{"id":"566669866109308e","type":"text","text":"\nmd_to_node\n\ninput\na large document\n\ndoes\nuses already existing md.py to break it down to md's to smaller md and make that each md to a node\n\nthis will happen after recon confirms the document is totally new\n\nreturns \na output folder path that has a lot of smaller mds\n\n","x":-4540,"y":5540,"width":774,"height":425},
		{"id":"8792d7b0c6010202","type":"text","text":"health:\n\ninput\nnull/node id\n\ndoes\ncalculate graph metrics like edge overlap etc, to make sure our graph is neithre too dense nor too sparse\n\nReturns \n\nstats object","x":-1900,"y":7156,"width":760,"height":329},
		{"id":"3cb42d627df044f1","type":"text","text":"get\n\ninput:\nnull\n\ndoes:\ndoes a global db query\n\nreturns\nreturn all nodes and edges (ids and summaries) for a UI representation\n","x":-2636,"y":6713,"width":736,"height":320},
		{"id":"78a661b2e0563d86","type":"text","text":"delete\n\ninput\n\nnode id\n\ndoes\ndelete that node and its related edges and synthetic nodes\n\nreturn\nnull\n","x":-1140,"y":6500,"width":466,"height":373},
		{"id":"0ddf56afc0f36231","type":"text","text":"UI Client\n\nThe client that actually queries to this and return answer, and helps it grow\n\nFrom  user perspective, it will only have one feature, chat and UI view of the graph, but we will plan here the MCP server which will connect the DB to the UI and show wiki, the graph etc and add stuff if user tell its to, or direct UI interactions like update etc?\n\n---\n\nQuery \n\nThis will be a subagent, rather than accumulating all mcp calls and result in the main chat history, we will have a subagent that does that and dies when user is satisfied\n\n\n---\n\nfeed\n\nIf a subagent response is good and the generated md is good, it adds it back to db and starts an ingest job\n\n---\n\nGet\n\nGet all the nodes and edges to view in sidebar\n\n---\n\nUpdate\n\nIf we manually change node, either add something to it, or change a fact, it should show a warning and the change should cascade back to its source nodes (rather than immeditate update, first add a warning, a user corrected this fact if the warning exists already and user corrects again then change the source itself)\n\n--- \n\nAdd a custom written node or deleting a pre made node and cascade other related nodes","x":124,"y":6687,"width":1180,"height":910}
	],
